Title: Series: Fasti di Napoleone
Description: Plate 18: Bonaparte's Egyptian campaign, showing an allegory of his return to France; nereids and seahorses in the left foreground gesture as his ship arrives in Frejus, right Engraving
Curator's comments: For comment on series see 1872,0113.684.1 This is the fifth of five plates on the Egyptian campaign. See "Mito e storia nei 'Fasti di Napoleone' di Andrea Appiani", Rome, 1986, n.xviii. See 1837,1130.1.19 for impression with production detail in scratched lettering naming G. Rosaspina as the engraver
Associated names: Associated with: Napoléon I, Emperor of the French (Napoleon)
Associated events: Associated Event: Napoleon's campaign in Egypt 1798-1799
